    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Awkward Dance</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Emily V Troiano letter commends Dec 17, 2006, query to Randy Cohen ethics column about reaction to black dancers in the Nutcracker, suggesting it shows self-awareness</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The writer to The Ethicist (Dec. 17) who asked if she was a racist because black dancers disturbed her viewing of ''The Nutcracker'' at least showed self-awareness. It's never too late to realize that, yes, you are a racist, and to try to ensure you aren't passing on those ideas to your grandchildren. It's talent and potential that are vital, not the color of one's skin.</p>
        <p>Emily V. Troiano</p>
        <p>Tucson</p>
      </block>
